dc:subject: Cranium
Undetermined
Thick Bone
Petrosals Porous/Atrophied
dc:description: Cranium has a loose calotte. All alveoli are resorbed, and the vault bone is thickened. The posterior petrosals extend posteriorly, intruding into the jugular canal (viz. on right). There is slight malformation of petrosal around carotid canal. Frontal sinus is extensive.

dc:memberOf.title: Ford Collection, UM Museum of Anthropological Archaeology
